<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,158,1048]" pageId="4" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,537,158,184]" pageId="4" pageNumber="97">Affinities and differentiation</emphasis>
:—Mexican populations of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephani (1916:" authorityYear="1003" box="[855,970,158,185]" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Anthocerotaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Anthocerotales" pageId="4" pageNumber="97" phylum="Anthocerotophyta" rank="species" species="subtilis">
<emphasis box="[855,970,158,185]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="97">A. subtilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are characterized by small, brown spores (26.6–42.1 μm), with papillate to tuberculate projections covering both proximal and distal surfaces. Within Mexican taxa, 
<emphasis box="[200,224,231,257]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="97">A.</emphasis>
aff 
<emphasis box="[275,418,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="97">sambesianus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Stephani, F." box="[428,671,230,257]" pageId="4" pageNumber="97" pagination="991 - 1008" refId="ref7648" refString="Stephani, F. (1916) Species Hepaticarum Vol. V. Geneve, 991 - 1008." type="book chapter" year="1916">Stephani (1916: 996)</bibRefCitation>
shares with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephani (1916:" authorityYear="1003" box="[820,935,230,257]" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Anthocerotaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Anthocerotales" pageId="4" pageNumber="97" phylum="Anthocerotophyta" rank="species" species="subtilis">
<emphasis box="[820,935,230,257]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="97">A. subtilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the small sized plants (
<bibRefCitation author="Ibarra-Morales, A. &amp; Muniz, M. E. &amp; Valencia, S." pageId="4" pageNumber="97" pagination="215 - 228" refId="ref6240" refString="Ibarra-Morales, A., Muniz, M. E. &amp; Valencia, S. (2015): The genus Anthoceros (Anthocerotaceae, Anthocerotophyta) in Central Mexico. Phytotaxa 205 (4): 215 - 228. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 205.4.1" type="journal article" year="2015">
Ibarra-Morales 
<emphasis box="[1392,1445,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="97">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
), up to 
<quantity box="[277,341,267,293]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="97" unit="mm" value="7.0">7 mm</quantity>
in diameter in 
<emphasis box="[507,524,267,293]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="97">A</emphasis>
. aff 
<emphasis box="[574,717,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="97">sambesianus</emphasis>
and up to 
<quantity box="[832,917,266,293]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" pageId="4" pageNumber="97" unit="mm" value="2.6">2.6 mm</quantity>
in length and 
<quantity box="[1074,1159,266,293]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="97" unit="mm" value="3.5">3.5 mm</quantity>
in width in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephani (1916:" authorityYear="1003" box="[1291,1402,266,293]" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Anthocerotaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Anthocerotales" pageId="4" pageNumber="97" phylum="Anthocerotophyta" rank="species" species="subtilis">
<emphasis box="[1291,1402,266,293]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="97">A. subtilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be differentiated by spore ornamentation pattern. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus (1753:" authorityYear="1139" box="[745,871,302,328]" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Anthocerotaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Anthocerotales" pageId="4" pageNumber="97" phylum="Anthocerotophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[745,871,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="97">Anthoceros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
aff 
<emphasis box="[918,1061,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="97">sambesianus</emphasis>
possess a low reticulated network with foramens and central sub-globose tubercles in triangular areas of proximal face (
<figureCitation box="[1123,1190,338,364]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1300,1322]" captionTargetBox="[182,1406,353,1275]" captionTargetId="figure-92@3.[182,1406,353,1275]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) micrographs of spores of Anthoceros subtilis and A. aff sambesianus. A–B. Anthoceros subtilis (from A. Ibarra-Morales 2019-14b) C-D. Anthoceros aff sambesianus (from A. Ibarra-Morales 19b). A &amp; C distal surface, B &amp; D proximal surface." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5814338" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5814338/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="97">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
C-D), while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephani (1916:" authorityYear="1003" box="[1337,1451,338,365]" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Anthocerotaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Anthocerotales" pageId="4" pageNumber="97" phylum="Anthocerotophyta" rank="species" species="subtilis">
<emphasis box="[1337,1451,338,365]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="97">A. subtilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
presents irregular tuberculate projections and minute papillae (
<figureCitation box="[837,903,374,400]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1300,1322]" captionTargetBox="[182,1406,353,1275]" captionTargetId="figure-92@3.[182,1406,353,1275]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) micrographs of spores of Anthoceros subtilis and A. aff sambesianus. A–B. Anthoceros subtilis (from A. Ibarra-Morales 2019-14b) C-D. Anthoceros aff sambesianus (from A. Ibarra-Morales 19b). A &amp; C distal surface, B &amp; D proximal surface." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5814338" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5814338/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="97">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
A-B).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,158,1048]" pageId="4" pageNumber="97">
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Peng, T. &amp; Zhu, R. - L." box="[344,565,410,437]" pageId="4" pageNumber="97" pagination="21 - 35" refId="ref6586" refString="Peng, T. &amp; Zhu, R. - L. (2013) A revision of the genus Anthoceros (Anthocerotaceae, Anthocerotophyta) in China. Phytotaxa 100 (1): 21 - 35. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 100.1.3" type="journal article" year="2013">Peng &amp; Zhu (2013)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephani (1916:" authorityYear="1003" box="[577,690,410,437]" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Anthocerotaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Anthocerotales" pageId="4" pageNumber="97" phylum="Anthocerotophyta" rank="species" species="subtilis">
<emphasis box="[577,690,410,437]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="97">A. subtilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Stephani (1916: 1001)" authorityName="Stephani (1916:" authorityPageNumber="1001" authorityYear="1001" box="[816,1205,410,437]" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Anthocerotaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Anthocerotales" pageId="4" pageNumber="97" phylum="Anthocerotophyta" rank="species" species="angustus">
<emphasis box="[816,947,411,437]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="97">A. angustus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Stephani, F." box="[954,1205,410,436]" pageId="4" pageNumber="97" pagination="991 - 1008" refId="ref7648" refString="Stephani, F. (1916) Species Hepaticarum Vol. V. Geneve, 991 - 1008." type="book chapter" year="1916">Stephani (1916: 1001)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in spore morphology, nevertheless, they can be differentiated by the presence of marginal spongy gemmae on the thallus margins of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephani (1916:" authorityYear="1001" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Anthocerotaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Anthocerotales" pageId="4" pageNumber="97" phylum="Anthocerotophyta" rank="species" species="angustus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="97">A. angustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, absent in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephani (1916:" authorityYear="1003" box="[365,480,482,509]" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Anthocerotaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Anthocerotales" pageId="4" pageNumber="97" phylum="Anthocerotophyta" rank="species" species="subtilis">
<emphasis box="[365,480,482,509]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="97">A. subtilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; and by the size of the pseudoelaters, which are considerably longer in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephani (1916:" authorityYear="1001" box="[1318,1452,483,509]" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Anthocerotaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Anthocerotales" pageId="4" pageNumber="97" phylum="Anthocerotophyta" rank="species" species="angustus">
<emphasis box="[1318,1452,483,509]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="97">A. angustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(40–496 µm) and somewhat shorter in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephani (1916:" authorityYear="1003" box="[569,680,518,545]" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Anthocerotaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Anthocerotales" pageId="4" pageNumber="97" phylum="Anthocerotophyta" rank="species" species="subtilis">
<emphasis box="[569,680,518,545]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="97">A. subtilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(42–199 µm). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephani (1916:" authorityYear="1001" box="[847,1080,518,544]" class="Anthocerotopsida" family="Anthocerotaceae" genus="Anthoceros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Anthocerotales" pageId="4" pageNumber="97" phylum="Anthocerotophyta" rank="species" species="angustus">
<emphasis box="[847,1080,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="97">Anthoceros angustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to Asia (
<bibRefCitation author="Peng, T. &amp; Zhu, R. - L." pageId="4" pageNumber="97" pagination="21 - 35" refId="ref6586" refString="Peng, T. &amp; Zhu, R. - L. (2013) A revision of the genus Anthoceros (Anthocerotaceae, Anthocerotophyta) in China. Phytotaxa 100 (1): 21 - 35. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 100.1.3" type="journal article" year="2013">Peng &amp; Zhu 2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
